<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626319>
    dc:description "FIGURE 51. A, B, Planes marinus (Rathbun, 1914), juvenile female, cl 7 mm, cw 8 mm (MZUSP 40330). C, D, Planes minutus (Linnaeus, 1758), ovigerous female, cl 12.9 mm, cw 13.5 mm (MZUSP 40257). Note in (C) setae on the upper anterior margin of the propodi of the pereopods 2–5 forming a natatory fringe (arrow); natatory fringe worn in (A). Habitus, dorsal (A, C) and ventral (B, D) aspects. Photographs by A. Pol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626319/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

